# OKV Workflow

Read [.cursor/skills/okf-vault/SKILL.md](.cursor/skills/okf-vault/SKILL.md) before any vault-related task in this repository.

## Command Routing

| Goal | Command | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Add new content | `/okv-ingest` | Interactive ingest wizard for one explicit source |
| Initialize `./knowledge/` | `/okv-init` | Repo-root setup with runtime adapters |
| Organize notes | `/okv-organize` | Bounded dossiers and curation proposals |
| Validate vault health | `/okv-validate` | Contract, manifest, graph, and recovery checks |
| Inspect graph | `/okv-visualize` | Manual graph visualization |
| Bootstrap a vault | `/okv-bootstrap` | Init plus validation |
| Ingest then validate | `/okv-ingest-check` | Composed ingest/check flow |

## Helper CLI

- Invoke `okv` as a child process with an argument array and pass `--json` for machine-readable results.
- Use the shape `okv <command> --json [args...]` for helper calls from agents.
- Treat stdout JSON as the agent contract and stderr as diagnostics.
- Do not shell-interpolate curator-supplied paths.

## Curator Rules

- Explicit sources only; never watch Drive, Granola, or filesystem paths automatically.
- One source at a time; complete acquire, validate, and commit before starting another source.
- Failure stop: after a source failure, offer retry, skip with reason, or abort. Do not silently continue.
- Deterministic gate: do not commit notes that failed helper validation.
- Helper-only Git transactions: use `commit` and `recover`; do not hand-edit managed vault paths during ingestion.
